Ideally, such a parameterization should be able to capture all relevant physics with the least number of parameters. Useful parameterizations can be motivated by predictions for specific theories of MG/DE [see 848] and/or by pure simplicity and measurability [see 41]. For instance, [980] and [278] use scale-independent parameterizations that model one or two smooth transitions of the modified growth parameters as a function of redshift. [115] also adds a scale dependence to the parameterization, while keeping the time-dependence a simple power law: 1.3.29\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
