The Symmetron. The symmetron model [436] is in many ways similar to the chameleon model discussed above. It requires a conformal coupling between the scalar field and the standard model and a potential of a certain form. In the presence of non-relativistic matter this leads to an effective potential for the scalar field 1.4.80\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
