Another possible way to build a theory that deviates from GR is to use a function of the second-order Lovelock function, the Gauss-Bonnet term G ≡ R2 − 4RμνRμν + RαβμνRαβμν. The Gauss-Bonnet term by itself is a topological invariant in 4 spacetime dimensions and does not contribute to the equation of motion. It is useful here since it avoids an Ostrogradski-type instability [967]. In R + f (G) models, the situation is slightly more complicated than for the scalar-tensor case, as 1.5.7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
