In the gravitational instability framework, inhomogeneities in the matter distribution induce gravitational accelerations g, which result in galaxies having peculiar velocities v that add to the Hubble flow. In linear theory the peculiar velocity field is proportional to the peculiar acceleration 1.7.38\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
