f-parameterization. This is in fact a non-parametric model in which the growth rate itself is modeled as a step-wise function fg (z) = fi, specified in different redshift bins. The errors are derived on fi in each i-th redshift bin of the survey.
γ-parameterization. As a second case we assume 1.8.4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
