The proper area of an infinitesimal surface at r, t = constant is given by A = R2(r, t) sin θ dθ dϕ. The angular diameter distance is the square root of A/ (sin θ dθ d ϕ) so that dA (z) = R (tp (z), rp (z)). Since the Etherington duality relation dL = (1 + z)2dA remains valid in inhomogeneous models, we have [530] 4.3.30\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
