				\begin{document}$\sum\nolimits_\alpha {\delta \rho {\alpha ^{({\rm{com}}{.})}} = 0}$\end{document}. Using the relativistic Poisson equation, one can verify that this implies that they do not contribute to the “curvature” potential.
